Pre-Game Insights: KEN is the clear favorite in betting odds, with a better recent form compared to MOZ.
Kenya has won three games while losing only two in their last five T20Is; they are coming off a 4-wicket win against Nigeria following a 14-run defeat against the same opponent.
Mozambique has lost three while winning only two games in their last five fixtures. They defeated Rwanda by 5 wickets in the previous T20I encounter.

The pitch seems to be bowling-friendly with an average of 125 runs in the last five T20s. Spinners have dominated here as compared to the pacers in the game. Rainy conditions expected, which could impact match proceedings.
